  <br /><br />
        Kim grew up in Eugene, Oregon and studied writing, music, and international relations abroad as a Student Ambassador to the United States. She graduated from North Eugene High School, and went on to focus on music, German, and creative writing, earning a B.A. from Pacific University. 
In her professional career, she has a wide variety of talents and experience in higher education as well as in private business. She has worked for The Oregon Graduate Institute and Pacific University in both collegiate and graduate university relations departments focused on alumni relations, fundraising, grant writing, and event coordination. She has also worked in the private sector in business technology based companies such as Trinity Technologies, Inc. and ECR Services.
Kim has also owned her own event consulting firm, Spectacular Events which specialized in large corporate fundraising events and unique private events for some of Portland’s elite.
Currently, Kim is co-owner of The ANDRESENGROUP and Livestock of America. She is a livestock broker, while also managing the publicity, marketing, and accounting side of the businesses. She helps livestock owners prepare their marketing with a focus on professional writing and marketing photography.

